    <a name="number-input"></a>
    <h3>Number</h3>
    <p>Number input type is well supported with our core browsers except noted exceptions below.   They support additional attributes for <code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, and <code>step</code>.</p>
    <p class="bg-warning">The notable exceptions are a lack of support in IE9 and lack of number type form spinner buttons for IE 10 &amp; IE 11.  See <a href="http://caniuse.com/#search=input%20type">caniuse.com</a></p>
    <div class="preview-section">
      <form class="form-content">
        <div class="form-section">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="numberTypeExample">Number:</label>
            <input id="numberTypeExample" name="numberTypeExample" type="number" name="numberType" class="form-control" placeholder="" min="0" max="200" step="10" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
    <div class="code-section javascript">
                        <pre>
  if (!Modernizr.inputtypes.number) {
  // initialize bootstrap touchspin
  $elms.TouchSpin({
  verticalbuttons: true,
  ...
  });
  }
      </pre>
    </div>
    <div class="code-section html">
                        <pre>
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&quot;numberTypeExample&quot;&gt;Number:&lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;input name=&quot;numberTypeExample&quot; type=&quot;number&quot; name=&quot;numberType&quot; class=&quot;form-control&quot; placeholder=&quot;&quot; min=&quot;0&quot; max=&quot;200&quot; step=&quot;10&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
      </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Date and Time</h3>
    <p>Date and time input types are much less supported in our core browsers.  <code>type="date"</code> should use native HTML5 when available otherwise it should use Bootstrap DatePicker.</p>
    <p>For <code>type="time"</code> we will need to use the Bootstrap Timepicker in most cases.  The native HTML5 control is problematic that it is only supported in Chrome and the mobile browsers with the limitation that you can not toggle between 24hr and 12hr time.  We will be using Bootstrap Timepicker along with custom validations unless 12hr time is an acceptable input.</p>
    <div class="preview-section">
      <form class="form-content">
        <div class="form-section">
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="dateTypeExample">Date:</label>
            <input id="dateTypeExample" name="dateTypeExample" type="date" name="numberType" class="form-control" placeholder="" min="0" max="200" step="10" />
          </div>
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="timeTypeExample">Time:</label>
            <input id="timeTypeExample" name="timeTypeExample" type="time" name="numberType" class="form-control" placeholder="" min="0" max="200" step="10" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
    <div class="code-section javascript">
      <pre>
  if (!Modernizr.inputtypes.date) {
  // initialize bootstrap datepicker
  $date-elms.datetimepicker(...);
  }
  if (!Modernizr.touch) {
  // initialize bootstrap timepicker. http://jdewit.github.io/bootstrap-timepicker/
  $time-elms.timepicker({
  minuteStep: 1,
  template: false,
  showSeconds: true,
  showMeridian: false,
  defaultTime: false
  });
  }
      </pre>
    </div>
    <div class="code-section html">
                        <pre>
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&quot;dateTypeExample&quot;&gt;Date:&lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;input id=&quot;dateTypeExample&quot; name=&quot;dateTypeExample&quot; type=&quot;date&quot; name=&quot;numberType&quot; class=&quot;form-control&quot; placeholder=&quot;&quot; min=&quot;0&quot; max=&quot;200&quot; step=&quot;10&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
  &lt;label for=&quot;timeTypeExample&quot;&gt;Time:&lt;/label&gt;
  &lt;input id=&quot;timeTypeExample&quot; name=&quot;timeTypeExample&quot; type=&quot;time&quot; name=&quot;numberType&quot; class=&quot;form-control&quot; placeholder=&quot;&quot; min=&quot;0&quot; max=&quot;200&quot; step=&quot;10&quot; /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>

